            <title>[KAFKA-17016] Align the behavior of GaugeWrapper and MeterWrapper</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17016</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MeterWrapper &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; can auto-recreate the removed metrics, but GaugeWrapper &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; can&apos;t. We should align the behavior in order to avoid potential bugs.&lt;/p&gt;


